           <li>{{ city }}: {{ items|map(attribute="name")|join(", ") }}</li>
         {% endfor %}</ul>
 
+    Like the :func:`~jinja-filters.sort` filter, sorting and grouping is
+    case-insensitive by default. The ``key`` for each group will use the
+    case of the first item in that group. Pass ``case_sensitive=true`` to
+    opt back into case-sensitive sorting and grouping.
+
+    You can pass ``with_counts=True`` to also get the number of items in
+    each group, without having to call ``|list|length`` on the group's
+    items. ``groupby`` then yields namedtuples of
+    ``(grouper, list, count)``.
+
+    .. sourcecode:: jinja
+
+        <ul>{% for city, items, count in users|groupby("city", with_counts=True) %}
+          <li>{{ city }} ({{ count }})</li>
+        {% endfor %}</ul>
+
+    .. versionchanged:: 3.2
+        Added the ``with_counts`` parameter.
+
+    .. versionchanged:: 3.1
+        Added the ``case_sensitive`` parameter.
+
     .. versionchanged:: 3.0
         Added the ``default`` parameter.
 
